      "appCustomProperties": {
        "state": "engineered",
        "edbb": {
          "role": "trading",
          "intro": "A cheap small-pad hauler that trades the Mk III's speed for a bigger hold: cargo first, a light shield to survive interdiction, and two medium multi-cannons as a deterrent. Initial is buy-only; A-rated is the trade baseline; Engineered stretches laden range and protected cargo.",
          "callout": {
            "label": "Shield, then fill the rest with cargo",
            "text": "Drop a bi-weave generator in one class-4 slot and pack everything else with cargo — ~74 tonnes protected, or ~92 unshielded if you'd rather run light. The Mk IV is slower than the Mk III (300 m/s boost vs 400), so keep thrusters and FSD A-rated and lean on the two medium gimballed multi-cannons to make a pirate reconsider."
          },
          "notes": {
            "MediumHardpoint1": "Deterrent medium multi-cannon; the single Corrosive Shell strips armour resistance so even a light gun bites.",
            "MediumHardpoint2": "Second medium multi-cannon; Auto Loader removes reloads so the deterrent never stops firing while you high-wake out.",
            "TinyHardpoint1": "One shield booster is the cheapest large multiplier on a thin trade shield; Heavy Duty stacks raw MJ.",
            "TinyHardpoint2": "Optional / low-priority — Ammo Capacity adds heat-sink charges. Dumps heat for silent running and Thermal-Vent resets.",
            "PowerPlant": "A-rated runs the shield, guns and core with margin; Low Emissions keeps it cool and light for range.",
            "MainEngines": "A-rated + Dirty Drives claw back what the heavy Mk IV loses on pace — the boost that gets a laden hold clear.",
            "FrameShiftDrive": "A-rated is the single biggest trade gain; Increased Range + Mass Manager maximise laden jump range.",
            "LifeSupport": "D-rate to save mass; Lightweight trims more — life support has no experimental effect.",
            "PowerDistributor": "D-rated feeds the boost and the low-draw multi-cannons; Engine Focused prioritises the getaway capacitor.",
            "Radar": "D and Lightweight — a trader needs no sensor range, so claw back the mass for jump range.",
            "FuelTank": "Stock 16t tank matches the laden jump range; fuel capacity cannot be engineered.",
            "Slot01_Size4": "Bi-weave regenerates fast under fire; Reinforced maximises its MJ and Hi-Cap adds more for surviving interdiction.",
            "Slot02_Size4": "Cargo — the Mk IV's extra class-4 slot over the Mk III is why it out-hauls its predecessor. Cargo racks aren't engineerable.",
            "Slot03_Size4": "Cargo space; worth it for dedicated haulers. Cargo racks aren't engineerable.",
            "Slot04_Size4": "Cargo space; worth it for dedicated haulers. Cargo racks aren't engineerable.",
            "Slot05_Size3": "Cargo space; worth it for dedicated haulers. Cargo racks aren't engineerable.",
